 medium for communication, sharing, and disseminating a considerable amount of human existence information. Daily and continuous communications imply the exchange of several types of content, including free text, picture, audio, and video data. However, OSNs face a large number of attacks that affects the privacy and security of users. Though there are many threats possible for the OSN users, the predominant threats are considered to be privacy and identity thefts. In this paper, a new community network is designed for enabling privacy security for the OSN users by offering them a secured and favorable network. The system isdemonstrated within a community. Feedbacks arecollected from the users to examine the performance of the new system. ANOVA single factor test is performed to analyze the variance between and within the groups from the collected data.","formulaStrippedArticleTitle":"An implementation of three layered NetChk two factor online social network model for privacy","pubLink":"/xpl/conhome/7190493/proceeding","allowComments":false,"doi":"10.1109/ICECCT.2015.7226012","rightsLink":"http://s100.copyright.com/AppDispatchServlet?publisherName=ieee&publication=proceedings&title=An+implementation+of+three+layered+NetChk+two+factor+online+social+network+model+for+privacy&isbn=978-1-4799-6084-2&publicationDate=March+2015&author=S.+Thiraviya+Regina+Rajam&ContentID=10.1109/ICECCT.2015.7226012&orderBeanReset=true&startPage=1&endPage=5&proceedingName=2015+IEEE+International+Conference+on+Electrical%2C+Computer+and+Communication+Technologies+%28ICECCT%29","endPage":"5","displayPublicationTitle":"2015 IEEE International Conference on Electrical, Computer and Communication Technologies (ICECCT)","pdfPath":"/iel7/7190493/7225915/07226012.pdf","publicationTitle":"2015 IEEE International Conference on Electrical, Computer and Communication Technologies (ICECCT)","startPage":"1","doiLink":"https://doi.org/10.1109/ICECCT.2015.7226012","issueLink":"/xpl/tocresult.jsp?isnumber=